div1.p: Office of the Sheriff of King County Washington Territory ss.

In obedience to the annexed writ of Habeas Corpus to me directed I do hereby certify that J. H. Smith was committed to my cusotyd on the 8th day of October 1888 and is now detained by virtue of a writ of Commitment, a true copy of which is hereby annexed. I also herewith produce said original writ of commitment.
Nevertheless I have the body of the said J. H. Smith now here before the Court as I am by said writ commanded.
Dated at Seattle W. T. this 9th day of Feby 1889 William Cochrane Sheriff of King County W. T. By M. Claddin Deputy.
Sheriffs Fees Taking up Prisoner 1.00 Copy of Writ .40 Travel 20 Return 50 .70 / $2.10
